-- EXCLUSIONARY CRITERIA (Not implemented in the query above, but can be added):
-- 
-- If two or more accounts share the same phone number AND also share the same 
-- street address, state, and zip code, they might represent a legitimate 
-- household (e.g., family members). To exclude such cases from the fraud alert,
-- you could add a WHERE NOT EXISTS clause that filters out accounts where the 
-- combination of (street_address, state, zip_code) is shared by more than one 
-- account with the same phone number.
--
-- Example implementation (to be added after the FROM clause or within a subquery):
--
--   AND NOT EXISTS (
--       SELECT 1
--       FROM workspace.default.customer_pii_sheet_1 c2
--       WHERE c2.Phone = c.Phone
--         AND c2.`Street_Address 1` = c.`Street_Address 1`
--         AND c2.State = c.State
--         AND c2.`Zip Code` = c.`Zip Code`
--         AND c2.Account_Number != c.Account_Number
--   )
--
-- This would remove accounts that have at least one other account sharing both
-- the same phone number and the same full address, assuming those are likely 
-- legitimate relationships. Adjust as needed for your risk tolerance.
-- =============================================================================
